<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Factorise the following expression completely:
<me>
{x^2-324}
</me>
</p>
<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We start by recognising the structure of the expression:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-324}
</me>
</p>

<p>
This expression has the form:
</p>

<p>
<me>
a^2 - b^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
The identity is the <alert>difference of two squares</alert>:
</p>

<p>
<me>
a^2 - b^2 = (a - b)(a + b)
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the two squares.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 = (x)^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
{18}^2 = ({18})^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
So here:
</p>

<p>
<me>
a = x \quad \text{and} \quad b = {18}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Apply the identity.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 - {18}^2 = (x - {18})(x + {18})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the factorised form is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x - {18})(x + {18})
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left(x-18\right) \left(x+18\right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>